channel.title: Soo retarted, someone with a brain answer this
channel.description: How come this section is full of the same questions over and over? Silab crap, runserver, compiling, port forwarding, no-ip, getting server to work, global objects, all crap that has a gillion tuts on it. And, when someone posts a question that you need you brain to answer, it doesn't get viewed, and doesn't get replied to! It's ridiculous, people come here for help, but only the noobs with the repeated questions get answers.

item.description:
@Waffles1 wrote:

True. How come non of my other threads get more than 1 glance from less than 5 people? I flame the community, and get a crap load of replies and views the next day!

sea crest:

people who ask the question over and over are people that do not play the computer 24-7 and have a life… give them some slack when u answer there questions.

I get sick of the same crap over and over again, when there are a crap load of tuts explaining them all.
